Constructor Detail

NewSessionCapability

public NewSessionCapability()
Creates an instance of Capability that can be used to create a session.

Before you can begin a session with a VERSANT database, you must create an instance of Capability. The Capability constructor enforces the rule that only one instance of Capability can be created inside each Java Virtual Machine. A single instance of Capability should be created by trusted code.

Throws a VException with the error code EVJ_ALREADY_CAPABILITY if you attempt to create more than one NewSessionCapability.

See Also:
FundSession
